        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class=""><strong>TIP:</strong> for irregularly shaped products, measure the largest dimensions to ensure the box will accommodate the entire product.</p><h4>STEP 2</h4><h3>Add extra space for comfort</h3><p class="">Your box shouldn’t be an exact fit to your product. Adding a small buffer ensures your product slides in easily and has room for any protective materials like tissue paper or padding.</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">Add <strong>3-5 mm (0.11 - 0.19 in)</strong> to each measurement for small products like droppers.</p></li><li><p class="">Add <strong>5-10 mm (0.19 - 0.39 in)</strong> for larger or heavier products like soap bars.</p></li></ul><h4>STEP 3</h4><h3>Choose the right box style</h3><p class="">Pick a box style that matches your product’s needs and packaging goals. Here are some popular options:</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg" data-image-dimensions="3000x2000" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=1000w" width="3000" height="2000" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/635172c6202bb8078a469eda/3f1b1eb0-6b46-4828-9e5c-84d40805eed4/bfgsna.jpg?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
          
          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <p data-rte-preserve-empty="true"><a href="https://www.socialgizmodesigns.com/shop/p/box-designs/flora-apothecary"><em>Vintage Floral Soap Box Template - Flora Apothecary</em></a></p>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><strong>Foldable boxes:</strong> Perfect for lightweight products like soap bars. If you’re using a Cricut machine, you can cut and score a single sheet of cardstock (200-250 gsm) or lightweight cardboard (around 300 gsm). Fold it neatly, and secure the edges for a sturdy design.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Rigid boxes:</strong> Great for fragile items like glass droppers. For these, use a thicker cardboard (around 400-600 gsm) to provide extra durability. With Cricut, you can cut panels separately and assemble them with glue to create a durable, polished box.</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Custom inserts:</strong> Ideal for products that need to stay firmly in place. Use cardstock (around 200-300 gsm) for lightweight inserts or thicker cardboard for heavier items. Cricut makes it easy to cut inserts that fit snugly around your product, providing extra protection and a professional look.</p></li></ul><p class="">When using Cricut, check that your design file is compatible, and adjust the material thickness settings to ensure clean, precise cuts. This will help you achieve a professional-looking box with ease.</p><h4>STEP 4 (optional)</h4><h3>Test your design with a mockup (advanced step!)</h3><p class="">You can create a quick test of your box dimensions to ensure accuracy. While this step is optional, if you’re feeling adventurous, you can create a simple mockup preview of your box by referring to the example below:</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
