  <h3>2. Evocative Logo</h3><p class="">Your logo is often the first impression potential customers have of your brand, making it a crucial element in establishing your identity. For a candle business, an evocative logo should convey the essence of your brand—whether that's tranquility, luxury, or sustainability. To achieve this, focus on incorporating meaningful symbols related to your candles and your unique brand story.</p><h3>3. Craft Unique Packaging</h3><p class="">Your packaging is more than just a container; it's a key part of the customer experience. For candle business, the packaging should be an extension of your brand story.</p><p class=""><strong>Eco-Friendly Materials:</strong> If your brand emphasises sustainability, use recycled or biodegradable packaging. Highlight this commitment on your packaging.</p><p class=""><strong>Sensory Experience:</strong> Think about how your packaging can engage multiple senses. Use textured materials, and include a small sample of another scent.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
